On Sun, 12 Dec 1999, Wakko Warner wrote:
> > system +-> head 1 +-> vt 1
> >        |          +-> vt 2
> >        |          ...
> >        |
> >        +-> head 2 +-> vt 10
> 
> You mentioned something about 2 keyboards?  How (standard din/ps2 and a usb
> keyboard?)
Thats one way. Also you can use the PS/2 mouse port to plug in a second
PS/2 keyboard. Be careful. You need to plug in the second keyboard after
you boot since some BIOS hang on having a keyboard plugged into a mouse
port. Their are patches for this.
> Does fbdev support the dual headed matrox g400 card?  I think it would be
> nice to have 2 heads, one for the 'main' machine and the other for logs
> (like a b/w, but I don't have room for another video card <g>)
Yes. Petr has been working on that recently. Look at matroxfb.txt. It has
his email address and email him for the patch.
